Defendant Moses Kelly in court with attorney Richard J. Carpenter.  Defendant Moses Kelly in custody.  Erin M. Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Court finds the State has complied with victim's rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing. 

AS TO COUNT 1-  
The Court WITHHELD sentence and placed defendant on probation for a period of 5 YEARS. If revoked, defendant to receive credit for 240 days time served. 

Conditions of Probation:
-No use of controlled substances;
-No contact with the victim;
-Participate in sex offender evaluation;
-Court set restitution at ZERO;
-Defendant is to be supervised by the Mental Health Unit of the Department of Corrections;
-Court WAIVED costs, fees and surcharges due to defendant's limited income;
-Defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Court will allow defendant to enter into a payment plan. 
-No unsupervised contact with children under the age of 16 years of age;
-Cooperate with the Department of Corrections and any recommendations for treatment or programming;

Filed:
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit form.
